      "body" : "> @luke-jr: Probably just need to calculate it twice when accepting to the mempool.\r\n\r\nAre you suggesting to continue to use `GetTransactionSigOpCost` for the [CTxMemPoolEntry](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/042c323922fce00a1cd0d955a0c8b8bfa80e4045/src/main.cpp#L1288-L1289), and count the sigops for the [non-standard check](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/042c323922fce00a1cd0d955a0c8b8bfa80e4045/src/main.cpp#L1296-L1298) seperately and accurately?\r\n\r\nThanks for the futher information @petertodd! I'm aware of the acutal cost, in terms of sigops allowed in a block, so I'm wondering, whether we can get away with counting the ops two times.",
